16 May 2016The Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) on University of Fort Hare Centenary celebration led by Minister for Performance, Monitoring and Evaluation in the Presidency, Jeff Radebe will hold a media briefing to provide status on the upcoming centenary celebration.Details of the briefing are as follows:Date:Wednesday, 18 May 2016 Time:12h00 Venue:Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament in Cape TownN.B: There will be a video link up to East London, 50 Church Street, Fort Hare East London CampusRSVP: Ireen Magwai (East London) Cell: 082 440 5676Andile Duka (Cape Town) Cell: 071 154 4519For more information on the centenary celebration, go to YouTube on the channel GovZA, twitter on @GovernmentZA and on the webpage: www.gov.za.Enquiries Nebo Legoabe Cell: 082 453 2874Issued by Government Communication and Information Systems (GCIS)